national public health authorities.
2. National public health authorities report to WHO on the areas in which
local chain(s) of transmission is/are occurring. These areas are provided
on the list of affected areas.
3. One death attributed to Hong Kong SAR occurred in a case medically
transferred from Viet Nam.
4. Since 20 Apr 2003 the United States of America is reporting to WHO
probable cases of SARS, therefore the number of new cases since last WHO
update is not applicable [in today's report - Mod.MPP].
